got bytes of hex from Apple
that we were suppose to Base64 encode, before sending it "back" to APple
But, first, we had to figure-out what we were working with

Why did I come-up with this solution?
(a) I didn't have docs on apple's format
(b) I didn't have any sample code that worked with the data
(c) I recognized that the input chunks (e.g. "7b0a0922" were really 8 hex #'s,
each 2char's long, i.e. 7b 0a 09 22
(d) I knew enough about "man ascii" to confirm that those represented the characters I wanted
(e) My grasp of pack & unpack is weak
(f) I was enjoying the challenge

Solution1: got.split.map {|s| s.scan(/../).map{|c| c.to_i(16).chr} }.join
Solution2: got.split.map{|hex_byte_string| [hex_byte_string].pack("H*") }.join

